---
title: Mushroom Lo Mein with Fresh Udon Noodles
description: Chinese-style lo mein gets a heartier and more wholesome twist when you swap out the usual meaty suspects for mushrooms and veggies like carrots and green beans. In this recipe, you’ll practice stir-frying udon noodles in sauce until they brim with a savory, soy, hoisin, and sesame-based flavor that explodes with each bite.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/mushroom-lo-mein-b54cd05f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/mushroom-lo-mein-0e9d27b0.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mushroom-lo-mein-592ddb0399052d1a683cb362
author: HelloFresh
time required: 35 minutes
course: main course
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 480 kcal
  fat: 17 g
  saturated fat: 2 g
  carbohydrates: 70 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 11 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 900 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Cut @green beans{6%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Peel and
mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Peel and cut
@carrot{1} in thirds, then cut each piece in half lengthwise and slice into
thin half-moons. Roughly chop @button mushrooms{4%ounce}. Thinly slice
@scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites separate.

Whisk together @soy sauce{1%tablespoon}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @hoisin
sauce{1%tablespoon}, @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, @honey{1%teaspoon}, and
@water{1/4%cup} in a #small bowl{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium
heat.

> TIP: If you have a nonstick pan, break it out.

Add @udon noodles{8%ounce} to pan and toss until tender, for ~{3-4%minutes}. If
pan seems dry, add a splash of water or drizzle of oil. Remove from pan and set
aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms,
carrot, and green beans and cook until lightly browned and softened,
~{5-7%minutes}, tossing occasionally. Add ginger, scallion whites, and garlic
and toss until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Reduce heat to medium. Add sauce and noodles to pan. Toss everything until
well-coated and sauce has thickened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide lo mein between bowls. Garnish with scallion greens.